Shami goes fuller outside off this time. Bavuma plants his front foot forward and drives it past mid off for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma blocks this off the back foot.
This one nips back in from middle off the length. Bavuma clips it to mid-wicket.
A full ball with a hint of away swing on off. Bavuma drives it off the middle of his blade straight to the short-cover fielder.
Another good ball by Thakur! A good-length delivery on middle that nips away from the batter. Kyle Verreynne defends it with the outer half of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne defends it solidly off the back foot.
A fuller delivery on off by Thakur. Kyle Verreynne defends it towards mid on this time. There is certainly some swing out there for both the bowlers.
A length ball, around off. The ball hits the green patch and bounces sharply. Kyle Verreynne defends it and it goes off the top of his blade. A single taken towards square leg.
A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma pushes this off the front foot and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the backward point region and the batters run two.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
Good-length delivery outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it comfortably.
Shami bowls this on middle this time. Kyle Verreynne clips it to fine leg for a single this time.

FOUR! A thick outside edge again and a boundary this time! A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma drives it on up and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies past the diving gully fielder and goes for a boundary.
Sharp bouncer from Shami angling into the body this time. Bavuma plays it awkwardly towards fine leg for a single.

Another delivery that is targeted into the body and is at an awkward height for Kyle Verreynne to defend. He hops and looks to defend. The ball hits his gloves and goes off the bounce to Pant behind the stumps.
A yorker this time by Shami on middle. Kyle Verreynne digs it out. This is brilliant stuff from Shami. After bowling two good short balls, he delivers a perfect yorker this time.
Touch fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it towards covers. The fielder there does well to dive to his right and half stop it. Saves three runs for his side.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne shoulders arms.
FOUR! Shot! Short of a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
WIDE! Bangs a bouncer, on off. Kyle Verreynne sits under it. Wide called for height.

FOUR! Another boundary! Kyle Verreynne is looking in good touch. Promising start for the wicket-keeper batsman who came in place of Quinton de Kock. Length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
On a good length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne shoulders arms.
Short and down the leg side. Temba Bavuma sways away from the line.
Good-length ball, around off. Temba Bavuma taps it to the off side for a single.

NOT OUT! Kyle Verreynne survives. Length ball, coming back in, on middle. Kyle Verreynne looks to work it on the leg side but gets an insidee edge onto the pads. Mohammed Shami appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. India opt for a review. UltraEdge shows there is a spike as the ball passes the bat. The original decision stands and India lose their review. India thought they had their man but will have to wait now.
A good short ball by Shami on middle this time. Kyle Verreynne ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne defends it towards the off side off the back foot.
Ohh..What a delivery to end the over! A good-length delivery around off. Nips back in sharply and cuts Kyle Verreynne into half. Beats him all ends up and goes back to the keeper.

Good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Temba Bavuma gets forward and looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals for an lbw but there was a clear inside edge there. The ball rolls to the off side and the batters take a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
In the channel again, outside off. Kyle Verreynne offers no shot.
On a length, down leg. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick but misses. Rishabh Pant dives to his left to collect the ball. India appeal for a caught behind but there was nothing on it.
Length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne jabs it to mid off.
Short ball, on middle. Kyle Verreynne ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma hops and tucks it on the leg side for a single.
On a good length, around off. Kyle Verreynne presses forward and blocks it out.
On middle and leg, defended to short mid-wicket.
Angling in a length ball, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne prods and looks to flick. He misses and gets struck on the pads. Jasprit Bumrah appeals for an lbw but that was going down leg.
Fuller, on middle. Kyle Verreynne squeezes it out to backward square leg.
On a length, on leg. Kyle Verreynne clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, around off, moving away. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Short of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne hops and blocks it from the crease.
Goes full, on middle. Kyle Verreynne gets his feet out of the way and pushes it to mid on.
Full again, outside off this time. Kyle Verreynne drives it to short extra cover.
Back of a length, on off, coming back in. Kyle Verreynne stands up on his toes and defends it on the leg side.
Siraj bowls this on a length, on middle. Bavuma defends it to short mid-wicket.
This one comes back in a little from the off stump line, off the length. Bavuma defends it again towards the on side.
A fuller ball, on middle. Bavuma drives it to mid on this time.
A good-length delivery around off and nips back in sharply. Bavuma leaves it watchfully.
A fuller ball on middle. Bavuma pushes it to mid on this time.
FOUR! Bavuma has found the gap this time! A length ball angling into middle and leg. Bavuma leans forwarda and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne defends it tentatively towards the off side.
Full and down the leg side this time. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick it but misses.
Bumrah bowls this fuller around off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it off the front foot to covers and gets a couple.
WIDE! Short ball on middle and it goes well over the batter's head. A wide called for height as Kyle Verreynne ducks under it.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone this time.
A short ball and around leg this time. Kyle Verreynne ducks under it comfortably again.
Bumrah goes fuller on middle this time. Kyle Verreynne defends it towards mid on. He is not getting a big stride in and could be a candidate for LBW.
Shorter length around off. Bavuma pushes this off the back foot towards covers.
Ashwin goes fuller on off this time. Bavuma defends this off the front foot this time.
A fuller ball on middle. Bavuma skips down the track and flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
A fuller ball on off. Bavuma pushes this back to the bowler. Ashwin needs to bowl little slower to get more purchase from the pitch.
This is eased to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Well bowled and well played! Tossed up, on off. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend. He plays it with soft hands though and the ball goes off the outside edge to third man for a brace.
A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma looks to defend but the ball seams away from him and beats the outside edge of his blade.
A fulll ball and down the leg side this time. Bavuma looks to flick it but misses.
Bumrah bowls this on off and fuller again. Bavuma pushes it to mid off and gets a single.
On a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne clips it to mid-wicket this time. Bumrah is looking for that LBW.
On a length and nipping back in from off. Kyle Verreynne defends it onto the turf.
On a length again and angling into middle. Kyle Verreynne defends it to mid-wicket this time.
Tossed up on off from 'round the wicket. Bavuma defends this off the front foot.
A fuller ball, on off. Bavuma skips down the track and clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter length this time on off. Worked towards the short leg fielder.
Quicker on middle. Defended towards the on side this time.
Flatter and shorter in length on middle. Kyle Verreynne clips it straight to short leg again.
Another flatter delivery by Ashwin on middle. Kyle Verreynne defends this off the back foot.
This is intense from Bumrah! A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma pushes it to point this time.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma defends this off the back foot back to the bowler.
On a length and nipping into middle. Bavuma works it to square leg.

FOUR! Bavuma has looked very comfortable so far and he has played a glorious shot now! An overpitched ball on middle. Bavuma drives it with full face of his blade and creams it through mid on for a boundary. Superb timing.
On a length and this one bounces a little low on off. Bavuma defends this off the bottom of his blade.
Back of a length, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Shorter length on off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to point.
A fuller ball on leg. Kyle Verreynne skips down the track and  clips it to fine leg for a single. 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Fuller on middle. Bavuma pushes this to long on as he skips down the track and gets a single.
Full and on the pads, clipped to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle. Kyle Verreynne prods and pushes it to mid on.
Slower through the air, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lunges forward and blocks it out.
FOUR! Bavuma gets another boundary. He is looking class apart here! A short ball, outside off. Bavuma quickly picks the length and cuts it through point for a boundary.
On a length this time with an inward movement. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Thakur goes fuller on middle this time. Bavuma drives it off the inside half of his blade towards deep square leg for a couple.
A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone this time.
Thakur hits the length hard again.  It is on the off stump line and Bavuma defends this off the back foot.
Back of a length with some extra bounce on off. Bavuma looks to defend but gets hit on his gloves.
Fuller on middle. Worked towards mid-wicket this time.
Again on the leg stump. Kyle Verreynne gets back and works it behind square on the on side for a single.
On middle and leg again. Bavuma flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle and leg and turning into the batter. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads. The ball loops in the air towards the on side.
A fuller ball and flatter on middle. Kyle Verreynne skips down the track and somehow manages to defend it.
Quicker on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks this off the back foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Bavuma cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Back of a length again, around off. Kyle Verreynne looks to cut but is unable to get any timing.
A good-length delivery outside off. Kyle Verreynne decides to leave it alone this time.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne pushes this off the back foot towards covers this time.
Another harmless delivery on a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Lord Thakur strikes again! A good-length delivery on off and that nips back in sharply. Kyle Verreynne is stuck on his crease as he tries to defend it. He misses and the ball hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger.  Kyle Verreynne reviews it but the Ball Tracker shows THREE REDS and Kyle Verreynne has to walk back. A big wicket for India as this partnership was building up and it is Shardul Thakur once again who provides the breakthrough. South Africa have lost half of their side now and India will be looking to quickly wrap this up now.
Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Full and on middle, Temba Bavuma steps out and clips it on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma works it to the leg side.
FOUR! That's a good shot! He moves into 40's now. Tossed up, on the pads. Temba Bavuma clears his front leg and works it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floats it up, on middle. Clipped to mid-wicket.
Full and on the pads, tucked to short leg.
SIX! Bavuma goes big! Ashwin bowls short, on middle. Temba Bavuma hangs back and pulls it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. Real intent from Temba Bavuma who is looking for his half century.
A full ball, on off. Jansen drives this off the outer half of his blade to sweeper cover for a single.

FOUR! Edge but safe and Bavuma gets to his fifty with a boundary! A good-length ball, around off. Bavuma looks to drive it and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies towards the third slip region for a boundary. This has been a fine knock from him.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shardul Thakur gets the first five-wicket haul of his Test career! What an occasion to get to your maiden five-wicket haul. Temba Bavuma walks down the track for some strange reason and Thakur pulls his length back around leg. Bavuma looks to clip it and gets a faint part of his blade. Pant behind the stumps dives to his left and takes a superb catch. Bavuma who was looking so good has to walk back and India are right on top now. There was some confusion regrading the catch taken by Pant but in the end replays show that he has taken it cleanly and Thakur is on a roll here.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Rabada leans forward and defends it towards the on side.
A good-length delivery around off. Rabada pushes this off the front foot square on the off side.
NO BALL! Back of a length on middle and leg. Rabada looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads and a leg bye is taken towards the on side. Thakur has overstepped here.
A fuller length delivery outside off. Jansen leaves it alone.
Shami bowls a full ball on off. Rabada looks to drive but fails to get the timing on that one.
Another full ball and this time Rabada drives it to covers crisply but Rahane stops it at covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and India are chipping in with some quick wickets here! Shami bowls this full on off again. Rabada goes for that expansive drive. The ball hits the inside half of his blade and loops in the air towards mid on. Siraj there takes an easy catch and South Africa are seven down now. Shami knew that Rabada is not going to resist the drive and he gets his man with that fuller delivery. Kagiso Rabada will be disappointed as he has the ability to bat but is gone now.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Maharaj is greeted with a short ball on middle. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
A good-length delivery outside off. Keshav Maharaj looks to push at it but gets beaten. Superb bowling.
A full ball, on off. Pushed to covers for a single this time.
A length ball, on off. Maharaj defends it towards the off side this time.
Another length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it towards the off side.
FOUR! A short ball and punished by Maharaj! A short ball on off and comfortable height for Maharaj to pull. He pulls it through square leg for a boundary. Lovely shot!
On a length, on off. Some extra bounce there and Keshav Maharaj dabs it square on the on side for a single.
A fuller ball on middle this time. Jansen flicks it to mid-wicket this time.
A length ball, outside off. Jansen lets it go this time.
Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it solidly towards the off side.
A good-length delivery on off. Keshav Maharaj plants his front foot forward and defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! What a good shot this is! Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj punches this off the back foot through covers for a lovely boundary. This guy can bat for sure.
Shami bowls a short ball on middle in reply to that boundary. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it and Pant behind the stumps does well to catch that.
On a length and nipping away around off. Keshav Maharaj pokes at it and gets a thick outside edge to point for a single.

Shami goes for a yorker on the last ball before Tea. It is very full on middle and Jansen flicks it to deep square leg for a single. So South Africa are 191/7 at Tea on Day 2 and are still trailing by 11 runs.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Marco Jansen looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pads.
Back of a length, on off. Marco Jansen hangs back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Poor from Shardul Thakur. Offers width, outside off. Marco Jansen takes the advantage and slashes it through covers for a boundary. The timing on that one was excellent.
Good-length ball, on top of off, coming back in. Marco Jansen is cut in half as he looks to defend. Good comeback by Shardul Thakur.
OUCH! Back of a length, on off. The ball shoots up after landing. Marco Jansen looks to defend. He misses and gets near the chest area. He looks in some pain.
Fuller and on off, Marco Jansen looks to drive. The ball goes off the inner half and knocks the stumps at the other end.
Fuller in length, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it to the off side.
Bangs a short ball, on leg. Keshav Maharaj sits under it.
Similar delivery like the previous one. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Fuller and on off, Keshav Maharaj drives it towards covers for a single.
Short ball, on middle, but the ball stays a touch low. Marco Jansen sits under it but gets hit on the shoulder. India appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no.

FOUR BYES! South Africa will take these runs however they came. Bumrah bangs a short ball, on middle and leg. Marco Jansen ducks under it. Rishabh Pant tried his best to stop the ball jumping but the ball hits his gloves and rolls back to fine leg for a boundary.
This is eased down to mid off for a single.
On a length, on off. Marco Jansen gets forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, on off. Marco Jansen stays solid in his defence.

In the air, but safe! Short of a length, on leg. Marco Jansen looks to pull. The ball goes off his gloves, hits him in the chest region and lobs up towards the leg side. Rishabh Pant charges ahead to catch the ball but falls short of him.
Back of a length, on off. Marco Jansen punches it to point.
Fuller, on the pads. Marco Jansen flicks it aerially towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs. South Africa now lead by 1 run.
On a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj does well to defend it out from the crease.
Similar line and length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj defends it to the off side.
Bangs a short ball once again, on middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line.
Short of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj cuts it to point for a single.
Fuller, outside off. Marco Jansen steers it to deep backward point for a single.
Full and slower, on the pads. Keshav Maharaj sits down on one knee and looks to sweep. The ball goes off the pads to fine leg for a leg bye.

Length ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj heaves it towards long on. Mohammed Siraj from mid on traces back but couldn't chase the ball and it falls short of him by quite a distance. Two taken. Shardul Thakur is not happy with that at all.
FOUR! Top shot! These runs will hurt India! Short of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj camps back and hammers it towards long on for a boundary.
On a good length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj throws the kitchen sink to this one as well but fails to connect.
On a good length, on leg, coming back in. Keshav Maharaj looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Fuller, on off. Keshav Maharaj drives it but straight to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj guides it to third man for a single.

WIDE! Bumrah bowls this short on middle. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line of the ball but it is anyways too high. Pant jumping to catch the ball fails to collect it cleanly and the batters take a bye. Wide given for height.
NO BALL! A beamer this time on off. Marco Jansen deals with it nicely and lets it go. That slipped out of his hands and will have to reload again.
Back of a length, on leg. Marco Jansen works it to deep square leg for one.

OUT! BOWLED! Jasprit Bumrah finally gets his first wicket and breaks this partnership! A full ball angling into the batter by going wide from the crease on middle and off. Keshav Maharaj makes room and looks to drive it but misses. The ball shatters the stumps and Keshav Maharaj walks back after playing a handy knock here. Not much celebration by the Indian players and rightly so as they were frustrated by this partnership. They will be looking to wrap this up quickly now.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: A length ball angling into middle. Duanne Olivier looks to defend but gets an inside edge of his blade onto the pads. There is a huge appeal from Bumrah but the umpire is unmoved.
NASTY! Bangs a short ball, on middle. Duanne Olivier turns away trying to sway away from the line. He gets hit on the elbow.
On a length, on off. Duanne Olivier defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
A fuller delivery on off this time. Duanne Olivier defends it towards the off side.
A full ball, on off. Marco Jansen hits this off the inside half of his blade towards deep square leg. He denies a single.
A yorker on off. Jansen jams it out over the bowler's head. The ball goes towards long off and the batters run two.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Marco Jansen heaves it across the line but misses.
A full ball, outside off. Jansen goes chasing for it but misses.
Back of a length, on off. Jansen defends it back to the bowler. Will he get a single off the last ball?
Jansen takes a risky run to retain the strike! Back of a length, on middle. Jansen works it to mid-wicket for a quick single. There is a shy at the bowler's end but misses. A single taken.
FOUR! Jansen is getting some valuable runs for South Africa! A short ball on off. Jansen pulls this time but gets the top edge. The ball flies over Pant and races towards the fence for a boundary.
A full ball, on off. Jansen makes room and lifts this towards long off. A single is denied again.
A yorker on off. Jansen digs it out. Good bowling this.
FOUR! Another boundary for Jansen! A full ball, on middle. Jansen stays deep in his crease and slams it wide of long on for a boundary. These are crucial runs for South Africa.
A good short ball by Bumrah in replay to that boundary. Jansen ducks under it.
Another nasty short ball on middle. Jansen ducks under it. Good quality action here.
Back of a length, around off. Duanne Olivier shoulders arms.

NOT OUT! A length ball on middle and nipping into the batter. Duanne Olivier looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits him on the pads and there is a huge appeal. The umpire is unmoved and Shami convinces Rahul to take a review.  The replays roll in there is nothing on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows wicket's missing. So Duanne Olivier survives and India are still searching for these last two wickets.
Length ball, outside off, nipping away. Duanne Olivier looks to play inside the line and misses.
Fuller, on off. Duanne Olivier pushes it towards covers.
Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Duanne Olivier looks to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Touch fuller, on the pads. Duanne Olivier defends it on the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! India needed a wicket and guess who provides the breakthrough, Lord Thakur again! A full ball on middle. Marco Jansen looks to heave it towards the on side. But gets a leading edge. The ball goes high in the air towards extra cover. Ravichandran Ashwin there takes a fine catch. India are just 1 wicket away now and they will be looking to wrap it up quickly now.
Howout: c Ravichandran Ashwin b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: On a length, outside off. Duanne Olivier lets it be.
Fuller in length, on off. Duanne Olivier drives it back to the bowler. The ball deflects off his hands and rolls back to mid on for a run.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shardul Thakur ends with seven wickets to his name. Hurls in a length ball, outside off. Lungi Ngidi has a feel for it. The ball goes off the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Rishabh Pant dives to his right to collect the ball. Shardul Thakur has been magnificent and has reaped rewards. SOUTH AFRICA ARE ALL OUT FOR 229. They lead by 27 runs.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Rabada starts with an off-target delivery. He bowls this down the leg side. Rahul lets it go.
Back of a length with some extra bounce targeting Rahul's body. He manages to work it behind square on the on side for a single. He is off the mark.
Mayank Agarwal gets a jaffa straightaway! A good-length delivery around off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
Back of a length on off. Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side this time.
An underedge this time. A full ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal looks to drive but gets an underedge towards first slip.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping away. Mayank Agarwal lets it go this time.
On a length, on the pads. KL Rahul turns it on the leg side by coming forward.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul punches this nicely off the back foot through covers and gets a couple. There was chance of taking a third run there but the batters were casual in their running.
A full ball, on off this time. Rahul drives it to mid off this time.
On a length, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone this time.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahul works it to short leg this time. Duanne Olivier seems to have lost some pace from the last time he played for South Africa.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul defends this back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal blocks it solidly off the back foot this time.
A good-length delivery outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone this time.
Another good-length delivery outside off and seaming away. Mayank Agarwal plants his front foot forward and lets it go.
FOUR! Full and wide and Mayank Agarwal is not afraid to play the drive on the up. Rabada bowls this full and wide outside off. Mayank Agarwal drives it hard aerailly over cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! This time an even better shot! Rabada bowls this fuller on off. Mayank Agarwal leans forward and creams it through covers for a lovely boundary.
Rabada pulls his length back a little this time, on off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads but height is an issue here. No damage done.
A full ball, on middle. Rahul pushes forward and defends it.
A short ball this time on middle. Rahul ducks under it calmly.
On a length, on off. Rahul plants his front foot forward and defends it solidly towards the off side.
Back of a length, around off. Rahul looks to push it off the back foot but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Back of a length, around off again. Rahul rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off and Rahul slashes it hard for a boundary. He plays it deliberately over backward point for a boundary. Positive intent shown by India here.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it towards the off side this time.
FOUR! Third boundary for Mayank Agarwal in no time! A full ball on middle. Mayank Agarwal prods forward and drives it through mid on for a boundary.
A boundary ball followed by a peach of a delivery! A good-length delivery around off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
FOUR! Poor delivery again and punished! A full ball on middle this time. Mayank Agarwal leans forward and flicks it wide of mid on for another boundary. Top-notch batting.
A fuller delivery on off by Rabada this time. Mayank Agarwal drives it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal hops and pushes it to point this time.
On a good length, on middle, angling in. KL Rahul tucks it to short leg.
Fullish, on middle. KL Rahul turns it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Beauty! Good-length ball, outside off, gets the ball to move away. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal stands up on his toes and blocks it out from the crease.
On a good length, on middle again. Mayank Agarwal taps it to mid-wicket.
Fuller this time, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal blocks it back down the pitch.
Starts with a good-length ball, around off, angling away. KL Rahul shoulders arms.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away. KL Rahul lets it sail through.
On a length, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, in the fifth stump channel, KL Rahul ignores it with ease.

OUT! TAKEN! Marco Jansen was lethal in the first innings and is the one who gets the breakthrough. He gets rid of a big fish here as KL Rahul is in a fine form. Jansen bowls a good-length ball, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul hangs back and looks to push it away from the body. The ball kisses the outside edge and carries through the second slip fielder where Aiden Markram catches the ball in front of him. Jansen starts celebrating but KL Rahul is not going anywhere and the umpire refer is upstairs. The soft signal is out. The third umpire checks the replay and he says that there is no conclusive evidence and rules that Aiden Markram's fingers were underneath the ball. KL Rahul has to walk back to the pavilion and South Africa have got just the start they were looking for.
Howout: c Aiden Markram b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Bangs a short ball, down the leg side. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves that one alone.
On a good length, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal clips it to the leg side.
On a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it out.

Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal hops and punches it off the back foot through covers. Temba Bavuma gives it a chase and slides in to stop the ball from racing away to the boundary. Saves one run for his side. Good commitment shown there by Bavuma.
On a length, on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara ticklels it to fine leg. He gets off the mark with a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal tucks it to short leg one-handedly. Oh, it came off the gloves infact.
Short of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal watches the ball sail past him.
On a good length, on middle, coming back in. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defened but gets hit near the box.
Length ball, on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara clips it past short leg for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal hops and defends it out.
Goes full this time, on off. Mayank Agarwal stays solid in his defence.
TWO BYES! Bangs a bouncer, on middle. Mayank Agarwal ducks under it. Kyle Verreynne jumps but fails to collect the ball. It rolls to fine leg and Dean Elgar does well to save a couple of runs.
On a good length, on top of off. Mayank Agarwal rocks back and blocks it from the crease.

Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. That's the length that caused problem to Pujara in the first innings. Some extra bit of bounce there as well. Cheteshwar Pujara has a poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Edged but safe! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge but falls just short of the first slip fielder.
Length ball, down leg. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara covers the line and presents the full face of the bat. He defends it on the leg side.
Fuller, on the pads. Clipped to mid-wicket.
On a good length, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara stands tall and blocks it out.
Back of a length and angling away from the batter. Agarwal hops and pushes it to point.
Jansen goes fuller this time on off. Agarwal pushes it to mid off. Rabada there dives full-length and stops it. Superb Stuff.
Jansen pulls his length back and bowls this outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
FOUR LEG BYES! Jansen bowls this on leg. Mayank Agarwal looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his thigh pad and races towards the long leg boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend but the ball hit him on the body and loops towards point.
FOUR! Short ball and punished by Pujara! A short ball around leg. Pujara hanga back and pulls this towards fine leg for a boundary. Positive start by Pujara.
A short ball again on middle. Pujara pulls this towards the fine leg fielder for a single this time.
FOUR! Beautifully played! A full ball, on off. Agarwal creams this drive towards extra covers for a lovely boundary.

OUT! LBW! Mayank Agarwal misjudges the line of the ball and pays the price. Big wicket for South Africa. A good-length delivery around off. Mayank Agarwal looks to leave it as he thinks it will seam away but it comes back in sharply and hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger immediately. Mayank Agarwal asks his partner whether to take a review or not but they decides against it. He walks back dejected. India have lost both their openers now and South Africa are right on top at the moment.
Howout: lbw b Duanne Olivier

Commentary: A good-length delivery outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leaves it alone.
Short ball, on leg. Ajinkya Rahane looks to pull but withdraws it in the end.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
Beaten this time! A good-length delivery around off again. Pujara looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
A full ball on middle by Jansen this time. Pujara clips it through mid-wicket and gets three runs. Good running there.
Back of a length, outside off and angling across and Rahane leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot towards covers for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara defends this solidly.
Back of a length, outside off. Rahane leaves this harmless delivery alone.
On a length, on off. Rahane defends this solidly.
Duanne Olivier goes fuller this time on off. Rahane drives it straight down the ground for a couple.
A short ball this time on middle. Rahane ducks under it.
There is that sharp bounce again. Back of a length on middle. Rahane manages to work it away behind square on the on side.

FOUR! Pujara is looking positive today and he gets another boundary now. A good short by Duanne Olivier on off. Pujara looks to pull but gets a top edge. The ball flies over the keeper and races away for the boundary. This is an important innings for both these players out in the middle.

On a good length, on leg, moving further away. Ajinkya Rahane looks to clip but misses. The ball goess off his hips and carries through to Kyle Verreynne. Stifled appeal for a catch but nothing there.
Length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it to cover.
On a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off, the ball stays a little low. Ajinkya Rahane looks to pull but misses.
Bangs in a short ball, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane takes his eyes off the ball as he looks to defend. He gets hit on the gloves.
Good-length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane prods and pushes it towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely played! Overpitched, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and drives it to long off for a boundary.
Length ball, angling away, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Short ball, down leg. Cheteshwar Pujara sways away from the line.
Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara lets it sail through.
On a length, on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara turns it to short leg. He has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Pujara was inside the crease though.
Back of a length, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara gets behind the line and hops. He blocks it out.
FOUR! Wow! Fuller in length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane drives it crisply through covers. Leans and plays it on the up to fetch himself a boundary. That's the Ajinkya Rahane we know!
Length ball, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane defends it out. No ball called as Kagiso Rabada has overstepped.
Jaffa! Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Ajinkya Rahane hops and looks to defend. The ball whizzes past the outside edge. Too good a delivery that.
On middle and leg, tucked on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out. That took off after landing but Pujara does well to negotiate it.
That has hit Cheteshwar Pujara on the thigh pad as he looks to flick this length ball.
Fuller in length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane taps it towards covers for a quick single.
FOUR! Top batting! Fuller in length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara steers it past point for a boundary.
Full again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara drives it to extra cover this time.
Angling in a length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.
FOUR! Aggressive batting this! Full again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara this time pushes it to long on for a boundary. South Africa are leaking runs here on the back-end of Day 2!
Length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane dabs it to gully. No ball called for overstepping.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Ajinkya Rahane glances it to deep square leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
On middle. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads. An appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Good-length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out.
Fuller, on middle. Pushed to mid on.
On the pads, clipped behind square on the leg side for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and defends it to the off side.
Full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara advances and pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara presses forward and defends it out.
FOUR! Drops it short and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and pounces on that one. Cuts it past cover-point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara ends the day with a boundary. Was a little bit streaky but he won't mind it. Loopy ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara presses forward and looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the slip fielder to third man for a boundary. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2! India lead by 58 runs!
Jansen starts with a full-length delivery on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot towards the off side solidly.
Jansen pulls his length back a little this time. It is around off and Rahane leaves it alone.
A full ball, on off this time. Rahane pushes this towards the off side and wants a single but is sent back by his partner.
Shorter length on off. Rahane pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets a couple. First runs of the day for Rahane and India.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rahane lets it go this time.
Back of a length around off. Rahane looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Good confident start by Rahane.
FOUR! Pujara continues from where he left off! A full ball and down the leg side. Pujara clips it fine to long leg for a boundary. Positive start for India.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pujara leaves it alone this time.

FOUR! Another boundary for Pujara and he is looking in good touch here. A full ball, on off. Pujara quickly picks the length and drives it through mid on for another boundary. The stand moves to 51 runs.
Ngidi pulls his length back a little, around off. Pujara leaves it alone.
On a length and nipping in a little from off. Pujara defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the on side.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara rides the bounce and pushes it to covers.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane rides the bounce and pushes it to square on the off side.
Length ball, angling down leg. Rahane stays back and looks to flick it but misses. The ball was very close to the blade. The bowler and the keeper make a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Back of a length, around leg this time. Rahane works it to fine leg for a couple.
FOUR! Sublime timing by Rahane and what a way to bring out the hundred for the team! A full ball, on off. Rahane leans forward and drives it straight back past the bowler for a lovely boundary.
Jansen pulls his length back and bowls this around off. Rahane defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone comfortably.

Big shout from South Africa but the umpire is unmoved! A good-length delivery on off and nips back in sharply. Pujara looks to defend but misses and gets rapped up on the pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar decides to not review it. The replays later show that the ball was going way above the stumps. A good decision by Dean Elgar to opt against the review.
Good-length ball, outside off. Pujara punches it hard towards point. The fielder there does well to make the stop.
Back of a length, around off. Pujara defends it towards gully.
Full length, on off. Pujara pushes it back to the bowler with soft hands.
An overpitched ball, on off. Pujara drives it straight to mid off this time.
This is the length where they need to be!  A good-length delivery on off. Pujara is well forward to defend it.
A full and hint of in swing there. This is around leg and Rahane looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit on the pads but it is down the leg side.
A length ball, on off this time. Rahane gets the inside edge onto his pads this time as he looks to defend.
A short ball and down the leg side this time. Rahane ducks under it.
SIX! Fantastic shot by Rahane! Short and wide outside off by Jansen Rahane picks the length quickly and cuts it over point for a maximum. This has  been a brilliant start for India.
A short ball on off this time. Rahane pulls this to deep square leg for a single.
A good-length ball, outside off. Pujara lets it go this time. Perfect start for India.
FOUR! Rahane is showing his class here! That's a decent delivery on a good-length outside off. Rahane cuts it touch aerially wide of gully for another boundary.
A fuller delivery on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Ngidi goes touch wider and bowls this fuller outside off again. Rahane leaves it alone.
On a length and nipping in from around off this time. Rahane looks to defend this off the front foot but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball goes behind square on the on side for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara defends this solidly off the back foot onto the turf.

FOUR! Soft hands by Pujara! A good-length delivery around off. Pujara gets forward and looks to defend the ball finds the outside edge of his blade and flies wide of the second slip fielder along the ground for a boundary.
NO BALL! Back of a length on off that bounces off sharply on off. Rahane defends this off the back foot. Rabada has overstepped here.
FOUR! Another boundary! Back of a length, outside off. Rahane punches this off the back foot through point for another boundary.
Back of a length, around leg. Rahane looks to work it away but misses.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane solidly defends this towards the off side.
Another slightly shorter length delivery on off. Rahane rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane swivels and looks to pull it away and gets hit on his body. This must've hurt a bit.
On a good length around off. Pujara defends this off the front foot onto the turf.
On a length and angling into middle. Pujara defends this off the outer half of his blade towards covers for a quick single.
A fuller ball, on middle. Rahane clips it to mid-wicket. The fielder there misfields and the batters get a couple of runs.
On a length, on off. Rahane solidly defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Ngidi bowls this on a good length, outside off. Rahane leaves it watchfully.
A full delivery on off to finish the over. Rahane drives it wide of mid off and gets a single.

FOUR BYES! A nasty short ball but it has beaten everyone. A good short ball on middle. Rahane looks to hook it but misses. Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps misses it too and the ball races away for the boundary. The lead is over 100 now.
On a length, on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot with soft hands.
FOUR! Rahane gets another boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Rahane defends this with soft hand and gets the outside edge of his blade. The ball flies through slip corridor for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Solidly defended off the back foot.
Another shorter length delivery on off. Rahane goes back and defends it off the backfoot again.
Short and down the leg side this time. Rahane lets it go.
Back of a length around leg. Pujara works it behind square on the on side for a single.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone watchfully.

Ohh..That has taken off! Duanne Olivier bowls this on a length and that hits the crack and bounce off sharply. Rahane tries to defend it initially but then sways away from the line of the ball. Good leave.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahane tucks it behind square on the on side for a single.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.

Fifty for Pujara in just 62 balls! This has been a fine innings from the fine player! He was playing for his place in the side and he delivers just when his team needed it the most. A length ball on middle. Pujara tucks it towards square leg and gets a single. Superb knock by the the number 3 batter and he will surely want to convert this one into a big hundred.
Good length, on the pads. Rahane stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

EDGY! The gully fielder and the man at second slip both left the catch for each other and in the end, the ball lands safely. Ajinkya Rahane riding his luck here. Back of a length, around off. This one flies off the deck. Rahane stays inside the crease and looks to defend it out. The ball hits him on the gloves and balloons towards the right to the second slip fielder. Aiden Markram was going for it but he thought Keegan Petersen is going for it and stops his runs towards the ball. No one gets there and Rahane gets across for a single.
Short ball, on off. Pujara ducks under it. Rabada has overstepped and the umpire signals a no ball.
Length ball, on the stumps. Pujara stays back and blocks it out.
Good length, sliding down leg. Pujara leaves it alone for the keeper.
Swing and a miss now! A beautiful delivery from Kagiso Rabada. A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Pujara looks to play away from his body but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short ball, on off. Pujara ducks it under without any hesitation.
Short ball, sliding down leg at a rapid pace. Rahane looks to pull it away but misses. The keeper moves to his left to gather the ball.

FOUR! Top placement! Rahane used the extra pace here. Good length, outside off. Rahane opens the face of the blade and steers it through the gap between backward point and gully for a boundary. The stand moves over 100 runs now.

FOUR! Ajinkya Rahane reads the delivery really well and gets his FIFTY in some fine fashion. Back of a length, on off. Rahane leans back and plays the ramp shot to guide it towards third man and finds a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Rahane leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, just outside off. The ball hits the crack on the deck and nips in a bit. Rahane hangs back and defends it out solidly.

Past the outside edge! Shout from some South Africans but the umpire is unmoved. A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Pujara presses forward as he looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Short ball, on off. Pujara sways away from the line of the delivery.
Fuller and on off. Pujara stays back and defends it to covers watchfully.
Does not carry! Back of a length, on off. Pujara hops inside the crease and defends it to short leg off his gloves. Luckily for Pujara, the ball lands short of the man placed there.
Good length, on the fourth stump line. This one flies off the deck. Pujara shoulders his arms at it and Kyle Verreynne gathers it above his head.
Outside off, Pujara has no stroke to offer.
Length ball, on leg. Rahane nudges it to square leg and gets across for a single. First runs after 9 balls for India.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Pujara sits under it and leaves it alone.

BYE! Misses everyone! A length ball, sliding down leg. Pujara looks to flick it away but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left but the ball evades him. The batters collect a bye. 150 now up for India.
Quick single! On the pads, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Full-length ball, outside off. This one bounces off the deck. Pujara shuffles across and shoulders his arms at it.
Good length, on off. Pujara hangs back and defends it out watchfully.

FOUR! Through the gap! A full-length ball, on off. Rahane stays back and drives it through covers. Marco Jansen gives it a chase and does well to keep the ball in play, as he goes on the floor beyond the rope. Temba Bavuma runs in and collects the ball to keep it down to three runs. Oh wait! The replays show Bavuma had his foot on the outline of the crease and hence in a boundary.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Length ball, on off. Rahane remains solid in his defense.
Good length, on off. Rahane defends it to the on side off the inner half.
Back of a length, outside off. Rahane shuffles across and leaves it alone for the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! Good pace and perfect line from Rabada gets a crucial breakthrough for his side. Back of a length, outside off. Some extra bounce off the deck. Ajinkya Rahane goes back and looks to defend it away from his body but misses. It takes the outside edge and Kyle Verreynne does the rest behind the stumps. Kagiso Rabada appeals for caught behind, the umpire takes his time and raises his dreaded finger. Rahane walks back disappointed after scoring an important fifty for his team. He would have loved to carry on but unfortunately for him Rabada has produced a beauty to get rid of him. This was the breakthrough South Africa needed.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Pujara defends it solidly towards the off side.
A fuller ball on middle. Pujara defends this towards short mid-wicket this time.
A short ball on off. Pujara sways away from the line of the ball this time.

NOT OUT! Cheteshwar Pujara survies and South Africa lose a review here. Length ball, outside off, shaping in. Pujara steps across and looks to defend it out but misses and gets pinged on the pads. Duanne Olivier pleads but the umpire is unmoved. After having a chat, Dean Elgar decides to take the review. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows the impact is outside the line and the decision cannot be overturned.
Length and outside off. Pujara guides it towards backward point.
On the pads, Puajra clips it towards deep square leg for a single.
Touch short, on the pads. Pujara clips it towards square leg for a single. Maybe this is what Rabada wanted. The new batsman on strike now.
FIVE WIDES! Not the start Rabada was looking for. Back of a length, on middle. Vihari ducks under it. The ball evades the keeper's attempt and runs into the fence at fine leg.
Swing and a miss! Rabada draws the batter forward this time. Fuller and outside off. Vihari looks to push it to the off side but misses.
Full length, outside off, nipping away. Vihari prods and shoulders his arms.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Vihari shoulders his arms at it.
Hanuma Vihari gets off teh mark now! Length ball, angled into the batters. Vihari clips it towards square leg and gets off the mark.

OUT! LBW! Kagiso Rabada strikes yet again and picks up his second wicket. He has been successful in sending back the two set batters in quick succession. A full-length ball, outside off, shaping in. Pujara presses forward and looks to defend it out but gets pinged on the pads first. Kagiso Rabada appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Pujara walks across to have a chat with Vihari and takes the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows three reds and this is trouble for India. South Africa have a sniff now and would hope they can capitalize on it.
Howout: lbw b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Length and on off. Vihari blocks it out solidly.
Fuller, on off. Hanuma Vihari drives it with soft hands towards the bowler. Olivier gets low and stops the ball sharply.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Hanuma Vihari ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
FOUR! Nicely timed! Hanuma Vihari gets his first boundary of the innings. A full-length ball, on leg. Hanuma Vihari keeps his balance and flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Length and on off. Vihari blocks it out solidly.
Swing and a miss! Good length, outside off, nipping away. Pant tries to push it away without any foot movement and gets beaten on the outside edge.

What a delivery! Back of a length, on off. This one flies off the deck. Pant stays back and looks to defend it out but gets it in front of slip cordon off the gloves. The players are being very chirpy with Pant on strike.

OUT! CAUGHT! The mind game works for South Africa if there was any and Rabada strikes again. Pant fails to start the new year on a good note. He is certainly not happy with himself. A good-length ball, outside off. Pant advances down the track and looks to cut it away but misses. The ball takes the outside edge and Kyle Verreynne collects the ball with ease. Kagiso Rabada appeals and the umpire raises his finger without giving it much thought. Kagiso Rabada has got his side back in the hunt. This is the magic of Test match cricket.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Good length, outside off. Ashwin looks to chase it but misses.
Length ball, on the stumps. Ashwin stays inside the crease and defends it out solidly.
Fuller and on off. Ashwin drives it towards mid off but not in the gap.
Back of a length, around off. Vihari defends this solidly off the back foot towards the off side.
Ohh...Another spicy delivery! A  short ball on middle and angling into body. Vihari sways away from the line of the ball.
Back of a length, around off. Vihari leaves it alone.
A full ball this time on off. Vihari drives it to mid on this time. This is turning out to be an intense passage of play.
A short ball on off. Vihari sways away from the line of the ball and looks to upper cut it but misses. Dangerous shot this under the situation.
On a length, on off. Vihari defends with soft hands and gets an outside edge to the slip corridor but along the ground.
Ohh...A leading edge but safe! Back of a length on middle. Ashwin looks to work it away towards the on side. But gets a leading edge towards point and the batters come back for a couple of runs.
A  length ball, on off. Ashwin drives it on up and aerially towards long off. The pair runs three this time. Good running.
Short and down the leg side this time. Vihari looks to pull but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Vihari leaves it alone watchfully.
Back of a length this time. Vihari defends it solidly off the back foot onto the turf.
Rabada goes fuller this time around off. Vihari drives it without any timing towards covers.
A short ball again on middle. Ashwin pulls it to fine leg this time. He is not going to miss out on any scoring opportunity.
Back of a length on off. Vihari works it to mid on this time.
Back of a length on middle. Vihari goes deep in his crease and works it past short leg for a single.
Nicely played by Ashwin! A short ball on middle. Ashwin pulls it along the ground to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on the body again. Vihari stays deep in his crease and defends it towards the on side.
Beaten! A good-length delivery outside off. Vihari leans forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
Jansen starts with a good short delivery angling into body from 'round the wicket. Ashwin looks to defend it off the back foot and gets a top edge towards the off side.
Back of a length again, around off. Ashwin looks to defend but ball zips past the outside edge of his blade.
FOUR! Top-class shot! Back of a length, on off. Ashwin rides the bounce and punches this off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
A short ball on off. Ashwin pulls this to deep square leg for a single this time.
Back of a length and angling into the body. Vihari looks to defend this off the back foot but gets beaten off the inside edge of his blade. This is the length he needs to bowl.
Back of a lenth, on off. Worked to short fine leg this time.
A fuller delivery on off. Ashwin drives it straight back to the bowler.

FOUR! DROPPED! Almost another wicket for South Africa. Back of a length, around off. Ashwin slashes this hard off the back foot this time. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball flies towards second slip. Aiden Markram jumps to catch it but fails to pouch it and the ball goes away for the boundary. Aiden Markram got his fingers there but the ball travelled quite fast off his blade.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ashwin departs now and it is one of the worst kind of dismissals for the batter. A length ball down the leg side and almost a nothing ball. Ashwin looks to clip it but gets a faint part of his blade. The ball goes behind the stumps and Kyle Verreynne moves to his left and takes an easy catch. South Africa gets another wicket and they have pulled back this game nicely now. Ashwin is a capable batter and this is a big wicket for South Africa. Can they restrict Indian lead to under 200 now?
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Back of  a length, on off. Thakur defends this off the inside edge onto his pads.

FOUR! In the air but safe! An overpitched delivery on middle. Thakur flicks this with good timing but hits it little aerially. The fielder at mid-wicket dives but the ball goes past him and Thakur gets the boundary.
A length delivery, on off and Thakur defends this solidly off the front foot onto the turf. So India are 188/6 at Lunch on Day 3. The lead for India is 161 now.
Extra bounce straightaway! A good-length delivery on off and this bounces off the length to hit Vihari on his gloves. He looks to defend and the ball loops towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Vihari leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Back of a length and down the leg side. Vihari looks to clip it but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and takes a good catch. Kyle Verreynne thinks there is bat invloved and convinces Elgar to go for the review. He takes it but the UltraEdge shows that there is no bat invloved. So Vihari survives.
NO BALL! A short ball on middle this time. Vihari ducks under it. Overstepping by Rabada.
Back of  a length, on off. Defended off the back foot.
Back of a length again by Rabada. Vihari defends this off the back foot solidly.
Length and on off. Vihari stays back and defends it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Thakur hits the boundary straightaway! Short and wide outside off. Thakur slams this off the back foot through covers for a boundary. He is an aggressive batter and will play his shots.
Back of a length, on off. Thakur watchfully defends this towards the off side.

FOUR BYES! Short ball and that bounces sharply to beat everyone! Back of a length, outside off. Thakur looks to upper cut it but misses. The ball goes over the head of the keeper and goes for another boundary.
Beaten this time. Back of a length and angling away. Thakur goes for the cut shot but misses.
FOUR! Smashed! Short and wide and Thakur is not going to miss out on that one. He stands deep in his crease and cuts this hard through point for a boundary.
A dot to end the over! An expensive over by Jansen comes to an end, 12 runs off the over. Good length, outside off. Thakur pushes it towards cover.
Back of a length, on off. Vihari defends this solidly onto the turf.
Back of a length, on off. Vihari blocks this off the back foot towards the off side.
Back of a length again but this time on middle. Vihari works it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Thakur defends this onto the turf. Thakur is key here for India.
A fuller ball and swinging into the batter. Thakur works it to short leg this time.
A good-length delivery around off. Thakur first thinks of defending it but then lets it go.
Back of a length angling on the body. Vihari plays it calmly by riding the bounce and defends it towards the on side.
A length ball, on middle. Vihari plants his front foot forward and defends it.
On the shorter side again by Jansen on off. Vihari defends this towards the off side off the back foot. He looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
Jansen bowls this on middle. Vihari works it to mid-wicket and gets a single.
Back of a length, on off. Thakur looks to cut it but is cramped for room and gets it to point.
Back of a length around leg. Thakur works it to fine leg for a single.
Rabada bowls this on a length on off. Thakur defends this back to the bowler.
Rabada goes short and bowls this around leg. Thakur pulls this to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length around leg. Vihari nudges it fine towards long leg and gets a single. Actually Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps half-stops it but they still get a single.
Back of a length on off. Thakur defends this off the back foot.

FOUR BYES! These runs will hurt South Africa! A full ball and down the leg side. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left to stop it but only manages to get a finger tip on it and the ball races away for a boundary.
A short ball to end the over. Thakur ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Worked to mid-wicket for a single.

SIX! Thakur continues on his merry way! Jansen goes short on middle. Thakur looks to pull but gets a huge top edge. The ball flies over the keeper for a maximum. He is a dangerous player and showing everyone why he is!
FOUR! What a shot! A length ball, on off. Thakur stays in his crease and just lifts this towards long off and one bounce over the ropes.
Back of a length, on middle. Thakur works it to short leg this time.

FOUR! Another boundary and Thakur is hurting South Africa here! A length ball, on off. Thakur heaves it across the line through mid-wicket for a boundary. Maharaj puts in a big dive near the fence but fails to stop it.

OUT! CAUGHT! The change of ball does the trick for South Africa! Thakur departs after playing a brilliant cameo here! Jansen goes short on middle. Thakur is in no mood to defend and pulls this aerailly towards deep square leg. He fails to get the distance and Keshav Maharaj there takes a good catch. So finally South Africa gets the breakthrough and end a superb innings by Thakur. Can South Africa bundle out India quickly now?
Howout: c Keshav Maharaj b Marco Jansen

Commentary: NO BALL! Length and on off. Vihari defends it towards short leg. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Back of  alength, outside off. Vihari guides it to third man for a single.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Shami looks to pull it but misses.
Back of a length on middle. Shami defends this towards the on side.
Rabada goes fuller on middle. Shami works it to mid-wicket this time.
Short ball this time by Rabada. Shami pulls it straight to Short leg.
Back of a length, on off. Shami rides the bounce and defends it onto the turf.
On a length, on off from 'round the wicket. Vihari defends it solidly.
A good short ball this time angling into middle. VIhari ducks under it.
Jansen bowls this on a shorter side again on the body. Vihari works it calmly towards short leg.
A full ball this time on off. Vihari drives it to long off for a single. Vihari is looking quite comfortable out there.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one strangled down the leg side. A length ball, around leg. It is a poor delivery by any sort of standard. Shami looks to clip it and gets a faint part of his blade. The ball goes to Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps and he makes no mistake. So Shami departs and Vihari will be critical for India from hereon.  South Africa would want to end this quickly now. The lead is already over 200. How much more will India be able to add?
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Back of a length, on middle. Bumrah makes room and looks to hook it away but gets beaten by the bounce.
Around the hips. Vihari tucks it to the left of the keeper.
Fuller, on leg. Vihari nudges it towards short leg fielder.
Two runs now! Touch short, around off. Vihari leans back and guides it through backward point. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
A dot now! Short ball, sliding down the leg side. Vihari swivels on the back foot and looks to pull it away but misses/
Length and down the leg side again. Vihari tries to chase it but misses.
Three dots in a row now! Vihari moves to the leg side. Kagiso Rabada follows the batter with a short ball. Vihari looks to ramp it over the keeper but fails to get any blade on it.
OUCH! Back of a length, on leg. Bumrah looks to heave across the line but misses and gets on his shoulders.
Short ball, down leg. Bumrah stays back and tries to hook it away but misses it completely.

Touch short, down leg. Bumrah continues to go for the pull shot but misses it yet again. He gets his on his shoulders for the second time in this over. Jasprit Bumrah just brushes his shoulders, as Jansen stares at him.

Short ball, on leg. Bumrah looks to pull it away but gets pinged on his shoulders. A repeat of the previous delivery. This time the players charge to the middle and exchange a few words before the umpire separates them.
Back of a length, on middle. Bumrah looks to heave it across the line but misses.
Fuller and on off. Bumrah looks to get under it and help it downtown but cannot connect this time.
NO BALL! Length and on off. Vihari pushes it towards backward point for a single. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
NO BALL! Length, on off. Bumrah chips it towards mid on but the ball meets the fielder on a bounce. Rabada oversteps yet again.
Fuller, on off. Bumrah works it towards mid off.

SIX! Bumrah connects and connects well enough to send the ball beyond the ropes. Good length, around middle and leg. Bumrah stays inside the crease and smokes it over the square leg fence for a biggie.
Back of a length, outside off. Bumrah makes room and looks to hit it away towards the off side but misses.
Back of a length, on off. Bumrah steers it towards third man for a single.
FOUR! Streaky! Full length, on off. Vihari throws his blade at it. The ball flies towards third man off the outside edge for a boundary. The lead moves to 217 runs.
Touch short, on middle. Vihari gets inside the line and pulls it to fine leg for a single. Vihari retains the strike.
Length, on off, blocked out solidly.
Full and on off. Vihari pushes it out.
On a length, on off. Vihari chips it towards mid off.
Back of a length, down leg. Vihari looks to chase it but misses.
Good length, on top of leg stump. Vihari makes room and looks to cut it away but misses.
Back of a length, sliding down leg. Vihari stays inside the crease and looks to pull it away but misses. A maiden for Jansen.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping in. Bumrah stands back and looks to defend it out but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lungi Ngidi gets his second wicket of the innings and Jasprit Bumrah holes out eventually. A length ball, around middle and leg. Jasprit Bumrah looks to heave it across the line. It takes the outside edge and balloons towards point. Marco Jansen runs back and takes a sharp catch. Jasprit Bumrah departs after hitting few lusty blows and that altercation with Marco Jansen has really fired him up.
Howout: c Marco Jansen b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: On off, blocked out solidly.
Length ball, sliding down leg. Vihari looks to flick it away but misses.
FOUR! Nicely played. Back of a length, around leg. Vihari goes back and helps it over the keeper for a boundary at third man. A top, top shot.
Fuller, on the pads. Vihari clips it to short mid-wicket and gets across for a quick single.
Length and outside off. Hanuma Vihari taps it towards point.
Full length, on middle and leg. Vihari defends it out watchfully.
A couple of runs now! Fuller, on middle and leg. Vihari flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. The batters push hard for two and get it comfortably.
Short ball, down leg. Vihari looks to chase it away but misses.
Fuller and on leg. Vihari drives it towards mid off for a single.
Siraj survives the last delivery of the over. Fuller, on middle and off. Siraj defends it to the off side watchfully.
Good length, on the stumps. Vihari blocks it out.
Length and outside off. Vihari taps it towards cover.
Length, on the pads, Vihari clips it towards square leg. Vihari sends back Siraj who was looking for a single.
Length and on off. Vihari defends it out solidly.
FOUR! The lead moves to 230 runs now. A short ball, on off. Vihari pulls it through mid-wicket and bags a boundary.

BYE! Vihari retains the strike. Short ball, down leg. Kyle Verreynne gathers the ball on his left but gives ample time for the bowlers to get across for a single. Hanuma Vihari retains the strike here.
Length, on middle and leg. Vihari clips it to mid-wicket.
Full and on middle. Vihari defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, outside off. Vihari guides it towards third man but does not get across for a single.
Length, on off, blocked out solidly.
FOUR! Hanuma Vihari is motoring along really well here. Olivier bangs in a short ball, outside off. Vihari hips and cuts it over the cover region for a boundary.
FOUR! This is great batting from Vihari. He is taking it away for India. Short ball, on leg. Vihari pulls it through square leg for a boundary. But now Mohammed Siraj to face the next over.

OUT! TIMBER! Lungi Ngidi does not waste anymore time and sends back Mohammed Siraj on a duck. Lungi Ngidi gets his third wicket of the game. A length ball, on the off stump. Mohammed Siraj stays inside the crease and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball goes through to rattle the off stump. Siraj cannot believe it. India get bowled out for 266 runs.
Howout: b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a good-length delivery outside off. It seams away sharply as Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Another delivery in that channel around off. Aiden Markram shoulders his arms again.
On a good length and slightly wider outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it watchfully.
He is getting good away shape here. Bowls this on a good length outside off. Aiden Markram carefully leaves it.
Another delivery on good-length with that away shape, Aiden Markram leaves it alone.

FOUR! A thick outside edge this time and that gives Aiden Markram and South Africa a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram pushes forward to defend with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes through backward point for a boundary.
On a good length outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
This time it is angled on middle. Elgar works it to fine leg for a single.
On middle and leg. A length ball and Aiden Markram works it to mid-wicket.
In that corridor of uncertainity around off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
FOUR! Aiden Markram gets his second boundary now. A length ball on middle. Aiden Markram leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Good shot.
Shami drifts on the pads again. Aiden Markram clips it past square leg. Vihari runs behind it and cuts it off. Three runs taken.
On a good length outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go. Too wide to make him play there.
Bumrah targets the stumps this time but end up drifting down the leg side. Aiden Markram looks to flick it but misses. Pant stops it with a good dive to his left.
Good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone carefully.
On a length, on off. Aiden Markram solidly blocks it towards the off side.
FOUR! Aiden Markram is dealing in boundaries at the moment. A length ball on middle and leg. Aiden Markram clips it through mid-wicket for another boundary. He is a fine player when he gets going.
A short ball to end the over on middle. Aiden Markram ducks under it.
A length ball and angling into middle. Elgar clips it to square leg.
Shami goes outside off this time and bowls this on a length. Elgar leaves it comfortably.
Shami bowls this around off on a good length. Elgar leaves it alone as it seams away.
Shami pulls his length back a little and bowls this on off. Elgar pushes it to covers and takes a quick single.
A good-length delivery outside off. It seams away as Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery outside off. Aiden Markram plants his front foot forward and lets it go. Aiden Markram is showing good foot movement so far.

FOUR! Elgar was not in total control of that but he has picked up the boundary! A good-length delivery angling away from the batter. Elgar pushes forward to defend and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies through gully and Elgar gets a boundary.
A good-length delivery outside off. Elgar lets it go this time.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone again.
Bumrah goes fuller outside off. Elgar pushes this square on the off side and gets a single.
On a length, on off. Aiden Markram solidly defends it towards covers and gets a quick single.
A length ball, on off. Elgar defends this solidly off the front foot. He gets this in the gap towards mid off and comes back for two runs.
Full and down the leg side this time. Aiden Markram looks to flick it but misses.

FOUR! Glorious shot from Aiden Markram! A length ball on off. Aiden Markram plants his front foot forward and drives it crisply through covers for a lovely boundary. He is a sweet timer of the ball and he showed all of it in that shot.
A good-length delivery outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
On a length on off. Aiden Markram solidly defends this towards the off side.
Shami goes fuller on middle. Aiden Markram pushes it to mid on this time.
A length ball, on off. Aiden Markram defends this solidly towards mid on. Aiden Markram is looking quite comfortable now.
Back of a length on middle. Elgar looks to defend but gets hit on the ribs.
He goes fuller this time around off. Elgar could have driven that but he decides to leave it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends this off the inside half of his blade towards the on side. A single taken.
This one stays low! A good-length delivery on middle. Aiden Markram watchfully defends it off the bottom of his blade towards the on side. A change of blade for Aiden Markram.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go this time.

FOUR! That's an edge but it doesn't carry and goes through the slip corridor for a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram defends it with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball falls short of the second slip fielder and sneaks through the gap for a boundary. South Africa are 34/0 at Tea on Day 3. They need 206 runs more to win this second Test match.
Runs straightaway for South Africa in the final session. Length ball, sliding down leg. Elgar helps it around the corner towards fine leg. The batters run two comfortably.
Good length, on off. Elgar defends it to cover off the outer half.
Two dots in a row! Good length, angled down leg. Elgar looks to flick it away but fails to get any bat on it.
Make it three dots in a row now! Nicely bowled. Quicker, on a length, around off. Elgar works it towards the slip cordon off the outer half.
Length, on the pads, Elgar flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Full length, on off. Elgar squeezes it out towards the man at gully.
Full length, outside off. Markram defends it out solidly. There are three men in the slips for Markram.
Fuller, on the pads. Markram flicks it to deep mid-wicket and collects a brace comfortably. The runs are coming easily now.
Length ball, on the stumps. Markram gets squared up and defends it back to the bowler.
Full length, angled into the batter. Markram defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
A single this time! Good length, outside off. Markram pushes it to covers with soft hands and gets across for a single.
Good length, around middle and leg. Elgar flicks it towards square leg for a single. South Africa need 198 more runs to win.
Fuller, on leg. Elgar stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket for just a single.
FOUR! Powerful hit! Length ball, outside off. Markram stays on the back foot and punches it through point to find a boundary.

BEATEN! Fuller and outside off, nipping in a bit. Markram prods and looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit high on the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals but the umpire is unmoved. KL Rahul thinks it is going above the stumps.

Length ball, on the pads. Markram looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shardul Thakur pleads yet again but the umpire shakes his head. It was clearly going down leg and hence KL Rahul does not take the review.
Swing and a miss! Markram looks all over the place here. Full length and outside off. Markram looks to drive it away but misses and Rishabh Pant collects it low and on his left.

OUT! LBW! Aiden Markram slips under pressure this time and it is the Lord Thakur who finds the breakthrough for India. It is really hard to keep him out of the wickets with the form he is in. A full-length ball, on off, nips in a touch. Aiden Markram presses forward and looks to defend it out but misses to get hit on the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals again but this the umpire agrees and raises his dreaded finger. Aiden Markram starts walking away straightaway and does not even think about taking the review. It was plumb. Breakthrough for India early in the final session.
Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Fuller, on leg. Elgar leans forward and defends it to the leg side.
Length and on off. Elgar blocks it out towards cover.
A single now! Fuller, outside off. Elgar works it to covers for a quick single.
BEATEN! This has come back a long way. On a length, outside off, nips in off the deck. Keegan Petersen looks to push it away from his body but misses.
OUCH! A length ball, around off. This one flies off the deck. Keegan Petersen misses his attempt to defend it out and gets hit near the ribs.
FOUR! Glorious shot! Fuller and outside off. Keegan Petersen leans in and creams it through the cover region for a boundary. A good end to the over for South Africa.
Length and on off, defended out solidly.
Fuller and outside off. Elgar blocks it out safely.
BEATEN! A length ball, angled across the left-hander. Elgar comes forward and looks to push it to the off side but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.
Past the outside edge! Good length, shaping across the batter. Elgar looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge..

A huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved! Some noise there but not off the blade. Thakur has been exception in the Test match with the ball. He gets his first maiden of this innings. He has asked a lot of questions since the last two overs. Good length, outside off, shaping away. Elgar looks to have a poke at it but misses.
FOUR! Keegan Petersen plays another lovely shot! A full ball on middle by Bumrah. Keegan Petersen leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
