Bumrah pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Keegan Petersen blocks this off the back foot towards the off side.
Back of a length on the pads. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit on the thigh pad and ball rolls behind square on the on side. A leg bye taken.
A short ball and angling into body from 'round the wicket. Elgar ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends it square on the off side.
On the stumps this time and again that shorter length. Elgar works it away behind square on the on side as his one hand comes off the handle. A single taken.
Thakur goes fuller on off. Elgar drives it back to the bowler.
A length ball and down the leg side. Elgar looks to clip it but misses.
Another length delivery around leg. Elgar works it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on off. Keegan Petersen defends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Thakur beats the blade of Elgar yet again! A fuller delivery around off. Elgar looks to drive but gets beaten off the outside edge of his blade. This has been a fantastic spell by Thakur.
A full ball again on off. Elgar drives it to mid off this time.
Shami is right on the target straightaway! A good-length delivery on off. Keegan Petersen defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Ohh..This one nips into the batter sharply! A good-length ball on off and nips back in. Keegan Petersen looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads. He nearly drags it back to the stumps.
A good-length delivery around off and this one nips away from the batter. Keegan Petersen lets it go.
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone again.
Back of a length on off. Keegan Petersen blocks it solidly towards the off side.
Shami goes fuller this time on off. Keegan Petersen lets it swing away and then pushes it to point.
A length ball, on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards mid on.
He hits the length hard and bowls this one on off. Elgar works it towards the on side for a single.
Thakur goes little fuller this time on off. Keegan Petersen is solid in his front foot defence.
Another fuller delivery on off this time Keegan Petersen pushes it to mid on.
A length ball on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen works it away wide of mid on.
That's a good leave! A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen carefully lets it go.
Shami bowls this on a length, outside off. Elgar decides to leave it alone.
FOUR! Nice little punch by Elgar! A full ball on middle. Elgar waits for it and then clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Good shot!
Back of a length, around off. Elgar leaves it alone this time.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a quick single.
This one keeps low. Second of the innings! A length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen defends this off the bottom of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Keegan Petersen defends this solidly yet again. Keegan Petersen is looking solid and has grown in confidence after the fifty in the first innings.

BEATEN! Shardul Thakur steams in from 'round the wicket. Good length ball, outside off. This one nips away off the deck. Elgar presses forward and looks to drive it towards cover but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, on the pads. Elgar flicks it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Played it late and gets a boundary. Length and outside off. Keegan Petersen opens the face of the bat really late and steers it towards third man for a boundary.
What a delivery! Short ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen looks to defend it out but pulls his blade back in time.
Fuller, on leg. Keegan Petersen flicks it towards mid-wicket. Cheteshwar Pujara gets low to his left to make the stop.
Three dots in a row to end the over for Shardul Thakur. Fuller, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen stays back and clips it towards short mid-wicket. Not in the gap though.
A sharp bouncer, wide outside off. Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Outside off, shaping away with some extra bounce. Elgar was caught in two minds but in the end he decides to leave it alone.
Full length, on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off. Elgar hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten.
Five dots on the trot! Very full and on off. Elgar defends it into the deck.

Second maiden of the innings for Shami. A great over by the seamer, asking plenty of questions. A length ball, angled into the pads. Elgar presses forward to defend it out but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Short and outside off. Tapped through point for a brace.
Short and outside off. Petersen works it towards point for a single.
Fuller, on off. Elgar defends it out solidly.
Outside off, Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Around the hips, Elgar stays back and tucks it to deep square leg for a single this time.
Good length, on top of off. Keegan Petersen steers it towards third man for a brace.
Fuller and on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
On a length, outside off. Elgar guides it past the man at gully for a couple of runs.
Good length, on off. Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
Full and on off. Elgar blocks it back to the bowler on a bounce.
Just two runs off the over! A good over by Shami. Full length, on off. Elgar defends it towards mid off.
Tossed up, outside off. Keegan Petersen shuffles across and blocks it towards cover.
Short and outside off, turning in. Keegan Petersen stays back and cuts it through point for a single.
A brace now! Floated, full and on off. Elgar leans forward to defend it out and does so with the outside edge. The ball goes towards third man and the batters run two.
Around off, Elgar blocks it watchfully.
Nice turn! Tossed up, full and on off. Elgar is drawn forward to defend it out but gets beaten by the away turn.
On the pads, Elgar nudges it towards square leg. A probing over by Ashwin. Some bounce and turn in his first over. Good signs for the spinner.
Siraj bowls this on a good length around off. Keegan Petersen lets it go as it nips into him.
FOUR! Keegan Petersen is on the attack and he has smashed this short ball! A short ball on off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses.
This one nips in sharply! A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen leaves it but the ball jags back in sharply and goes just over the off pole.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Back of a length to end the over on off. Keegan Petersen solidly defends it.
Ashwin drifting on the pads. Elgar clips it through square leg for a single.
A fuller ball on leg and turning in. Keegan Petersen looks to flick it but misses. Pant fails to collect it cleanly and a bye is taken behind him.
A flatter ball, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
A fuller ball on off. Elgar defends it watchfully back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up on off. Elgar defends it off the front foot this time.
Tossed up again, around off. Elgar leaves it alone as it turns away sharply. Elgar is a key man here for South Africa.
Back of a length and angling into the body. Keegan Petersen looks to defend but gets hit high on his pads.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen rides the bounce and punches it to deep cover for a single.
A good-length delivery, angling away from the batter. Elgar leaves it alone.
Another length delivery around off by Siraj. Elgar carefully lets it go.
Siraj goes fuller and wider outside off. Elgar is not interested in playing that one.
In that channel around off. Elgar watchfully lets it go again.
Shorter and flatter by Ashwin on off. Keegan Petersen blocks this off the back foot.
Shorter again on off. Keegan Petersen cuts it to point for a single this time.
Fuller this time on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on middle. Worked to mid-wicket this time.
Ashwin tosses this up around off. Elgar leaves it alone.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Defended off the front foot solidly.
Back of a length around leg. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses. He gets hit high on the pads but no damage done.
Siraj goes fuller this time on middle. Keegan Petersen drives this off the inside half of his balde and gets it to deep square leg for a couple.
Siraj pulls his length back a little this time and bowls this on middle. Keegan Petersen works it to deep square leg for just a single this time.
A short ball on middle by Siraj. Elgar carefully ducks under it.
Good-length delivery around off. Elgar is in no mood to play that one.
Siraj goes fuller this time outside off. Elgar resists driving and lets it go.
A fuller ball on middle. Defended solidly back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! Ravichandran Ashwin strikes! This is a huge wicket for India. This partnership was looking quite threatening and Ashwin provides the crucial breakthrough! Slightly shorter delivery on middle and turning in. Keegan Petersen looks to clip this off the back foot but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a huge appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Ravichandran Ashwin is elated. Keegan Petersen has a chat with Elgar and decides against taking a review. So India have finally got the second wicket and can they capitalise on this breakthrough now?
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: A flatter ball on middle. Defended off the back foot.
Slower in the air on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends it towards short leg this time.
Tossed up on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends but gets the inside edge on his blade and ball falls just short of Pujara at leg slip.
Quicker and flatter delivery on off. Defended off the back foot this time. End of a brilliant over by Ashwin.
Bumrah bowls this on a good length outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Bumrah bowls this shorter on off. Elgar is solid in his defence.
Ohhh... In that channel around off. Dean Elgar decides to let it go.
An effort ball from Bumrah. He bowls this short on middle. Elgar ducks under it rather comfortably.
Bumrah goes fuller and Elgar drives it through covers. Ashwin chases it and cuts it off. Three runs taken by the batters.
Back of a length around leg. Rassie van der Dussen pulls it to fine leg for a single. Ashwin will now get the chance to bowl at Rassie van der Dussen.
Nice drift there for Ashwin. He bowls this around off. Rassie van der Dussen gets back and plays it late behind square on the off side for a single.
Drifting on the pads and Elgar tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A shorter length delivery on middle. Rassie van der Dussen somehow manages to work it towards short leg.
A full ball and Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot. Almost got him there Ashwin. Pant is having fun behind the stumps.
A flatter ball on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it square on the off side.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the front foot. Ashwin is all over Rassie van der Dussen here and has Pant for his support with some quite funny and sarcastic talks.
Good length, angled across the left-hander, on off. Elgar defends it out off the bottom end of his blade.
On a length, outside off. Elgar stays back and shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, on the pads. Elgar stays back and blocks it to the leg side.
Four dots in a row! A sharp bouncer, around off. Elgar leaves it alone. Pant leaps and does well to get a hand on it. Saves a certain boundary here.
OUCH! That is a solid blow! Short ball, around off. Elgar hangs back and gets hit straight on his helmet. A well-directed bouncer by Bumrah. Pant rushes towards the batter to have a check on him.
A bouncer now, on off. Elgar ducks under it. Pant does well to pluck it from the air. A maiden over for Bumrah.
Floated, full and on off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid off.
Risky leave but Rassie van der Dussen trusts the bounce here. Tossed up, around leg. Some extra bounce off the deck. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms and gets hit high on his pads.
Short and outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it to point for a single. 100 is up for South Africa.
Full and outside off. Elgar leans in a defends it out.
Full, on the pads. Elgar clips it to short mid-wicket.
Looped up, full and outside off. Elgar defends it out watchfully. Just a single of the over. Great over by Ashwin.
Full and on off. Rassie van der Dussen stays inside the crease and gets his blade down in time to defend it out.

Touch short, on the bodyline. Rassie van der Dussen stands back and pulls it to deep square leg. Mohammed Shami runs across to his left from fine leg and stops the ball with his legs. Shardul Thakur recovers the loose ball and keeps it down to just a couple.
Full length, on middle. Rassie van der Dussen helps it towards mid on.
Length, on the pads, Rassie van der Dussen clips it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Outside off, shaping away from the left-hander. Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Just three runs off it. South Africa aren't able to score as freely as they did early on. A sharp bouncer, on off. Elgar leaves it alone. Pant flies in the air to make a good stop.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it towards cover for a single.
Floated, full and on leg. Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.
Flighted, full and on middle. Elgar defends it out solidly.
On the pads, Elgar clips it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Full and on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Elgar remains solid in his defense.
Short ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen has no stroke to offer.
Length ball, on the fourth stump line. Rassie van der Dussen shuffles across and defends it out.
Length ball, wide outside off, nipping away. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone for the keeper.
Nice movement on this one! On a length, outside off. This one nips in off the deck. Rassie van der Dussen leans back and leaves it alone watchfully.
A length ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pats it towards point and gets a single.
Another run now! Full length, on the pads. Elgar flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off. Elgar defends it out watchfully.
Tossed up, outside off, some extra bounce now. Elgar defends it to the off side.
Looped up, around off. Elgar prods and gets an inside edge onto the pads. Ashwin appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, defended out solidly.

Full and outside off, Elgar leans in and drives it through the cover region. Mayank Agarwal gives it a chase and pulls it back it time but he might've injured his knee in the process. The batters run three. Mayank Agarwal remains outside the ropes and the physio has a look at it.
Carrom ball, on off. Rassie van der Dussen presses forward and blocks it out solidly.
A single now! Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar is surprised by the bounce and is taken back by it. He works it towards point off his gloves. The batters cross for a single.

This one stays low! Full length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen gets his blade down in time to defend it towards square leg off the inside edge. Both the batters have their work cut out here. They have faced various variations in the last couple of overs. Won't be an easy task to end the day with a smile on their faces.
Thakur bowls this back of a length around leg. Elgar clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length again on middle. Rassie van der Dussen works it to mid-wicket.
On a length with nice bounce for Thakur. Rassie van der Dussen defends this solidly onto the turf.
A good-length delivery to end the over. He bowls this outside off and Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone. South Africa need 126 runs more to win.
Length ball, outside off. Elgar defends it out solidly.
Fuller, outside off. Elgar guides it towards gully.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar looks to leave it alone but gets hit on his right hand. Elgar is not looking confident in the middle.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Elgar stays back and ducks under it.
Full, angled into leg. Elgar flicks it towards fine leg for just a single.
Full length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it to the off side solidly.
Length ball, down leg. Elgar clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Rassie van der Dussen.
On a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on leg. Rassie van der Dussen clips it to fine leg for a run now.
Length and on off. Blocked out solidly.
BEATEN! Lovely shape. Good length, outside off, moving away. Rassie van der Dussen looks to chase it but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it out solidly.
Short and on the bodyline. Rassie van der Dussen puls it to square leg for a single.
Back of a length, ouside off. Elgar leaves it alone at the last minute.
Length, on off. Elgar defends it out watchfully. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3.

Ohh...What a delivery to start! A good-length delivery angling into the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his balde as it seams away quite sharply. This will be interesting.
On a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this solidly towards the off side this time.
Drifting on the pads this time. Rassie van der Dussen looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit on the thigh pad and ball rolls away towards long leg. Two leg byes taken. First runs of the day.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it solidly towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone this time.
On a length, on off and seaming away a little. Rassie van der Dussen defends this towards gully.
A tossed up delivery on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Drifting on the pads Ashwin. Elgar looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls away towards fine leg. Three leg byes taken.
Quicker on middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen works it to short leg.
Slower in the air on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the front foot.
Ashwin goes 'round the wicket and bowls this fuller on off. Driven back to the bowler.
Ashwin bowls this fuller  on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends and ball loops in the air just away from short leg.
On a length from 'round the wicket on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot onto the turf.
Bumrah goes little fuller on middle. Elgar pushes this off the inside half of his blade to deep square leg for a single.
Ohh...A good ball this time. Coming in with the angle on off and is bowled on the good length. Rassie van der Dussen defends it onto the turf.
FIVE WIDES! Bonus runs for South Africa! A short ball on middle and leg by Bumrah but it is way too high and goes over the batter and keeper for a boundary. Wide called for height.
A fuller delivery on middle this time. Rassie van der Dussen clips it to mid-wicket for a single. Slight misfield there.

A fuller delivery again on middle. Elgar flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. Will India continue with Ashwin in the next over? The conditions are overcast and seamers will definitely get good help here.
On a length, on off. Elgar is solid in his front foot defence.

Ohh.. Rassie van der Dussen goes back to the fuller delivery. A full ball on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot and gets the inside edge behind square on the on side for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle. Worked to mid-wicket this time.
Tossed up on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Flatter on middle. Defended by Elgar off the back foot.

FOUR! Elgar plays a beautiful shot to get to his fifty! This has been a superb knock by South African skipper. A fuller delivery on middle. Elgar clips it wide of mid on and gets it in the gap for a boundary. He has been a rock for South Africa in this whole series. Can he take his team over the finish line?
Very full again by Ashwin on middle. Elgar flicks it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
Well left! This lands outside off, extra bounce. Rassie watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Well defended! Good length and on off, this lands and takes off, Rassie defends with one hand off the handle.

That was a nasty delivery. Luckily for Rassie, it goes over the gully fielder! Length and on off, it lands and then takes off. Rassie looks to defend but it goes off the shoulder, it flies above the head of the gully fielder and towards third man for two.
Going down leg! Angled into the pads, Rassie looks to flick but misses! It hits the pad, a huge appeal but turned down. That is going down leg.
Solid! On off, blocked again. End of an action-packed over.
On a length from 'round the wicket angling into the stumps. Elgar defends it towards mid on.
Shami pulls his length back a little on off. Elgar defends this off the back foot onto the turf.
A good-length delivery around off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Shami goes short this time and bowls this on middle. Elgar ducks under it. There is definite ploy of bowling short and then going fuller.
On a length, on off and coming in with the angle from 'round the wicket. Elgar defends it from his crease.
Another length delivery on off. Elgar defends it solidly again.
On a good-length on off. Rassie van der Dussen works it away towards the on side.
Ohhh...This one is in that channel around off and seams in. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it and thankfully for him it dosen't strike the off stump.
This one bounces sharply off a length. On a length on off. This one nips in and hits him high on the pads as he tries to defend it.
A fuller delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it through covers for a couple.
On a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot solidly.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery on middle. Elgar drives it to mid on this time.
Shami pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it comfortably.
Drifting on the pads and a easy single given to Elgar. He clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen rides the bounce and punches it to covers for a single. Fifty partnership between these two. Crucial one in the context of the game.
Shami beats him all ends up this time! A good-length delivery around off from 'round the wicket. The ball first comes in with the angle and then seams away to beat Elgar who tries to defend it.
Back of a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone comfortably.
On a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
A good-length delivery around off and seaming into the batter. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Bumrah bowls this on a crack around good-length. Rassie van der Dussen looks to flick it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.

FOUR! Classy shot by Rassie van der Dussen! Slightly overpitched on off. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and drives it crisply off the middle of his blade through covers for a lovely boundary. South Africa need just 93 runs now. India need wickets quickly here.

Ohh.. Bumrah is quite consistently hitting that area near the crack. He bowls this on a good-length around off. The ball nips in sharply with extra bounce and Rassie van der Dussen gets the inside edge onto his pads as looks to clip it.
A fuller ball on middle. Elgar pushes it to mid on for a single.
FOUR! Another boundary and pressure is building on India now! A fuller delivery on middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Rassie van der Dussen is turning the heat on! A quick bouncer on off by Shami. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and pulls this in front of square for another boundary.

FIVE WIDES! This is the second time this has happened today! A short ball on middle that is too high for the batter to connect and even for the keeper to collect. It goes over Pant and for a boundary. Wide called for height.
A fuller delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it to point.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot solidly.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone watchfully. An expensive over from Shami and South Africa are right on the top now.
Thakur starts with a length ball, down leg. Dean Elgar glances it towards fine leg and collects a run.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Rassie van der Dussen stays back and defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Edgy! Back of a length, just outside off and curling away late. Rassie van der Dussen looks to drive on the up but it goes off the outside edge past the slip cordon and into the fence. Had there been a gully in place, it would have been straight to him.
Length ball, around off and bouncing sharply off a length. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but it goes off the inside half of the blade towards square leg for a run.
Good-length ball, around leg. Dean Elgar nudges it towards deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! What a shot! This was slightly shorter in length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen stands tall, rides the bounce nicely and punches it through the cover region for a boundary. Runs are coming thick and fast for the hosts!
Length ball, jagging back in from middle. Dean Elgar turns it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.
Back of a length, nipping back in sharply. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away a bit. Rassie van der Dussen prods to defend but it whistles past his outside edge. Lovely delivery from Shami!
On a length, angling in from off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run.
Short of a length, jagging back in from off. Dean Elgar gets on top of the bounce and defends it on the leg side.
Another delivery, on a length and nipping back in from outside off. Dean Elgar gets behind the line of the ball to block it.

A loud shout for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Good-length ball, jagging back in from outside off and taking off from a length. Rassie van der Dussen prods to block but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
BEATEN! Length ball, outside off and curling away late. Rassie van der Dussen presses forward to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
On a length, way outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to this one.
Thakur goes fuller and wider, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, just outside off. Rassie van der Dussen prods to block but the ball takes from a length and hits him high on his blade.
Full ball, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.

That is a peach of a delivery from Shami! Good-length ball, angling in from outside off and then shaping away a bit after landing. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend but he misses as the ball goes past his outside edge.
On a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
Short of a length, angling in from off. Rassie van der Dussen gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no. Full ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.

OUT! TAKEN! Mohammed Shami gets his reward and this is a much-needed wicket for India! Beautiful bowling. When you are so consistent, there is bound to be a ball with a batsman's name on it. On a length, just short of full, outside off, Rassie van der Dussen plays at it tentatively. He is neither forward nor back and pushes at it. The ball comes in with the angle but after pitching, the ball moves away late. That squares van der Dussen up and he tries his best to follow the ball. But all he can manage is an outside edge, which goes straight into the hands of Cheteshwar Pujara at first slip. The game opens again. South Africa need 65 runs. India need 7 wickets. Game on.
Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
BEATEN! Top delivery from Shardul Thakur! Good-length ball, around off and angling across the batter. Elgar hangs back to block but the ball zips past his blade.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Dean Elgar tucks it to the leg side.
Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar taps it towards point.
Full ball, outside off. Dean Elgar prods and pushes it to mid off.
Thakur drags his length back and hursl a good-length ball, on leg. Dean Elgar clips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shami bowls this back of a length, outside off. Elgar lets it go. Elgar is critical here for South Africa.
Angling into off from 'round the wicket. It is fuller. Elgar solidly defends it.

FOUR! Elgar goes hard and gets an edge but over the slip corridor! A length ball, outside off. Elgar slashes hard at it and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the slip corridor for a boundary.
On a length and around off. Elgar defends it square on the off side this time.
Ouch! That might have hurt him! A full ball on off. Elgar looks to drive but gets the inside edge onto his back leg. He is a tough character and looks fine.
Good-length delivery outside off. Elgar decides to leave it alone.
Thakur bowls this on a good length outside off. Bavuma lets it go.

DROPPED! Heart-in-mouth moment for India and South Africa. But cannot blame the bowler here. Such catches either stick or they don't. Full, around off, Temba Bavuma looked to drive straight. But the ball hit a patch of grass and bounced a tad extra. Hence, it hit the higher part of the bat. As a result, Bavuma was unable to control the shot and spooned it straight back. Now, Thakur is a right-arm fast bowler and when he is running from over the wicket, the momentum takes him to the left. But the ball comes to his right. Thakur realizes it but perhaps goes a bit too early, being a bit too anxious. He maybe, anticipated the ball to come quickly but it came a tad slower. He stuck his right hand out but the ball hit his palm and dropped down.
On a length, on off. Bavuma is well forward and just pushes it to deep cover for a single. He is off the mark.
A short ball around leg this time by Thakur. Elgar ducks under it comfortably.
Thakur bowls this on a shorter side again on middle. Elgar rides the bounce and works it to mid-wicket.
A good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone. 59 more needed for South Africa to win this game.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma defends this off the back foot and the ball goes towards the on side. A single for Bavuma.
FOUR! What a shot! Elgar leading from the front! A full ball on off. Elgar drives and brings that bottom hand into the play and gets this past mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! Back of a length and Elgar gets another boundary! Shami bowls this slightly shorter around off. Elgar rides the bounce and opens the face of his blade a little and gets it through the gully region for a boundary. Ajinkya Rahane at gully puts in a dive to his left but the ball goes past him.
Back of a length on middle. Elgar defends this towards the on side.
Shami goes little fuller on middle. Elgar defends it solidly again.
A good-length delivery around off. Elgar defends it with soft hands towards point.
A length ball, on off. Bavuma solidly pushes it to covers.
There is still enough movement for Indian bowlers to trouble the batters. A good-length delivery around off. The ball nips in sharply as Bavuma leaves it alone.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it comfortably this time.
Thakur hits that crack around off this time. Bavuma looks to defend but the ball bounces sharply to hit him on the gloves.
A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone. It goes the other way this time.
Slightly fuller on off. Bavuma pushes it to deep cover and gets a single.
Shami bowls this on a good length outside off. Bavuma lets it go. Some away movement for Shami there.
Back of a length with that upright seam. Bavuma defends this off the back foot solidly.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone. They need to make Bavuma play here.
Shami almost finds the edge this time! A good-length delivery around off. The ball nips away a little and beats the outside edge of the blade as Bavuma tries to defend it.
Back of a length with some extra bounce. Bavuma looks to defend it but gets a leading edge towards covers for a single.
Shami goes fuller on off. Elgar pushes this towards the off side. His one hand comes off while playing that shot.
Good running! Length ball, nipping back in from off. Bavuma looks to flick but it goes off the inside half of the blade towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Thakur goes fuller on middle. Bavuma drives it to mid on this time.
Length ball, well outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders his arms to this one.
Fuller in length and jagging back in from off. Temba Bavuma presses forward to block this one out.
Another ball, fuller in length but way outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, around off. Bavuma presses forward and blocks it to the off side and yells a loud 'NOOO'. South Africa need 46 more runs - India need 7 wickets to seal the series!
Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar stays back and blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Dean Elgar stays back, opens the face of his bat and works it to deep backward point for a single.
Length ball, jagging back in from outside off and staying a touch low. Temba Bavuma blocks it out in the end.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
FOUR! Top shot! This is a fuller-length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma prods and carves it past the diving cover fielder to fetch himself a boundary.
NO BALL! Banged into the deck, outside off. Temba Bavuma sways away from the line of the ball. No ball called by the umpire as Bumrah oversteps.
NASTY! Short of a length, around off and taking off from a length. Bavuma stays back to block but it hits the shoulder of his bat and luckily for Bavuma it falls safely on the off side.
Wide! Siraj bangs it into the deck, outside off and going over the batter's head. Dean Elgar lets it be and the umpire signals it as a wide for height.
Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar works it behind square on the off side for a single.
Short of a length, outside off. Bavuma stays back and punches it past the cover fielder to collect a run.
Back of a length, around leg. Dean Elgar hangs back and clips it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Back of a length, around off. Temba Bavuma rides the bounce nicely and blocks it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma stays back, opens the face of his bat and steers it to deep backward point for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar taps it towards backward point and takes a quick run. South Africa are just 34 runs away from a historic win! India badly need a wicket or two here!
Back of a length, angling in down leg. Dean Elgar ducks underneath.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Dean Elgar turns it to the leg side for a run.
Back of a length, around off. Temba Bavuma looks to block but it goes off the outside edge towards Ajinkya Rahane at gully, on the bounce.
Short of a length, jagging back in from middle. Temba Bavuma turns it towards mid-wicket.
This is a back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Temba Bavuma gets behind the line of the ball and defends it.
FOUR! That is a top shot from Bavuma! Full ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma presses forward and caresses it nonchalantly through the cover region for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely done! Banged into the deck, around leg. Dean Elgar rides the bounce nicely and pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder for another boundary.

FOUR! Three boundaries in a row and Dean Elgar seems to be in a hurry to finish things off now! Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar hangs back and steers it through the slip cordon to bag another boundary.
FIVE WIDES! Oh, dear! Nothing going India's way now! Short of a length, around off. Dean Elgar lets it be and the ball flies over Rishabh Pant to race away towards the fence.
Short of a length, around middle. Elgar blocks it out.
FOUR! AND AGAIN! Siraj bangs it into the deck, around off. Elgar stays back and ramps it over the slip cordon to fetch himself yet another boundary. South Africa are just 12 runs away from a win now!
Leg bye! Back of a length, down leg. Dean Elgar misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls away towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Short of a length, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Dean Elgar cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Temba Bavuma prods and blocks it out.

NASTY! Hanuma Vihari seems to be in serious pain as he gets struck on his right shoulder. This was tossed up, around middle. Bavuma gets down on his knee to sweep but he hits it straight to Hanuma Vihari at short leg. The ball hits Vihari on his right shoulder.
Flatter ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Loopy ball, turning down leg. Temba Bavuma looks to flick it but misses.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Temba Bavuma presses forward and blocks it out watchfully. South Africa need just 10 runs to win the game and level the series 1-1.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar turns it past the mid-wicket fielder for a run.
Length ball, way outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
On a length, around off. Temba Bavuma prods and defends it to the off side.
Full ball, outside off and shaping away late. Temba Bavuma looks to drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
FOUR! That is a cracking shot from Bavuma! A bumper, around middle. Bavuma swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Length ball, angling in from leg. Temba Bavuma clips it to the leg side for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and carves it to deep cover for one.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Bavuma nudges it towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single. South Africa need just 1 run to win!
Loopy ball, around off. Dean Elgar looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the blade back towards the bowler.

FOUR! There it is! Dean Elgar, South Africa's skipper hits the winning runs and he is pumped! Ashwin tosses it up, around middle. Elgar heaves it over the mid-wicket fielder and finishes things off with a boundary. What a chase this has been from the Proteas! Dean Elgar, take a bow! SOUTH AFRICA WIN THE MATCH BY 7 WICKETS AND LEVEL THE THREE-MATCH SERIES 1-1!
